tr.td: Title: OV - multiple issues
Author: Akande, Olusina

1. Essential hypertension I10
Chronic, controlled.
Complicated by nothing.
Meds: No change in management
Labs: Future labs sent.
Imaging: EKG not on file
Counseled on lifestyle changes such as low salt diet, activity, and excess alcohol.
2. Gastro-esophageal reflux disease without esophagitis K21.9
Chronic, partially controlled.
Meds: Continue H2 therapy
No suspected reflux complications (barret/stricture).
Lifestyle: wt loss, avoid meals 2-3 hrs before bed.
3. Hypothyroidism, acquired, autoimmune E06.3
Chronic, stable
Labs: TSH sent.
Meds: Continue current medication.
Counseled on healthy activity and diet.
4. Mixed hyperlipidemia E78.2
Chronic, stable.
Most likely due to genetic expression.
ASCVD: Pending labs
Meds: No changes in management
Imaging: None.
Discussed healthy lifestyle.
5. History of CVA (cerebrovascular accident) without residual deficits Z86.73
Chronic.
Meds: Continue antiplatelet and statin
Referral: None
Continue to work towards optimal BP and glycemic control.
6. Aneurysm, cerebral I67.1
Subacute, stable.
Patient claims to have had aneurysms seen on imaging.
Most recent MRI and MRA reports do not mention anything about aneurysms.
Request for further documentation sent.
7. Keratoconus H18.609
Chronic
Has follow-up with corneal specialist to develop prescription contacts.
Patient to follow-up in 6 months for Medicare wellness.
